description: |
  Docs structure based on mint.json. Use these sections and paths when linking or organizing content:

  - Documentation: Core guides live under these directories
    • /overview/** (introduction, quickstart, concepts, architecture, caching)
    • /ingestion/** (uploads, objects, buckets, collections, namespaces, features)
    • /processing/** (feature-extractors, batching, model-tuning, tasks, pipelines)
    • /retrieval/** (retrievers, interactions, research)
    • /enrichment/** (taxonomies, clusters)
    • /operations/** (security, deployment, observability)
    • /troubleshoot/** (errors, limits)

  - API Reference: Autogenerated from OpenAPI
    • /api-reference/** (health, organizations, namespaces, buckets, bucket-objects, bucket-batches, feature-extractors, collections, collection-documents, retrievers, retriever-stages, taxonomies, clusters, tasks, webhooks)
    • OpenAPI source: mint.json.openapi
    • API base URL(s): mint.json.api.baseUrl

  - Integrations:
    • /integrations/** (object-storage: overview, s3, gcs, azure-blob, r2, wasabi, tigris)

  - Studio (UI):
    • /studio/** (quickstart, namespaces, buckets, collections, taxonomies, clusters, retrievers, research)

  Linking guidance:
    • Prefer linking to the above doc pages over embedding raw endpoint strings
    • Avoid legacy paths like /management/* or /search/*
    • When showing endpoints, omit version prefixes in examples
globs:
  - overview/**
  - ingestion/**
  - processing/**
  - retrieval/**
  - enrichment/**
  - operations/**
  - troubleshoot/**
  - integrations/**
  - studio/**
  - api-reference/**
alwaysApply: true
